
# Sine wave generator I/O

## MCC inputs

| Input | Function                    |
|-------|-----------------------------|
| InA   | Frequency modulation source |
| InB   | Amplitude modulation source |


## MCC outputs

| Output | Function                    |
|--------|-----------------------------|
| OutA   | Frequency and amplitude modulated sine wave |
| OutB   | Frequency modulated sine wave |


## MCC control registers

| Control register| Function                    |
|-----------|-----------------------------|
| Control0  | Sine wave frequency control|
| Control1  | Sine wave amplitude control|
| Control2  | FM depth|
| Control3  | AM depth|

### Control0

Sine wave frequency = $\frac{Control0 \times Clk}{2^{29}}$  Hz
The frequency modulation would be limited to supporting only positive frequency shifts.

### Control1

Sine wave amplitude = $\frac{Control1 \times 4}{LSBs/volt}$  Volt

### Control2

Amplitude modulation = $\frac{InA \times Control2 }{2^{36}}$  Volt

### Control3

Frequency modulation = $\frac{InA \times LSBs/volt \times Control3 \times Clk }{2^{45}}$  Hz

For details on the clock rate and LSBs per volt across different platforms, please refer to [MCC documentation](https://apis.liquidinstruments.com/mcc/io.html).
